%N A395378 Numbers that are sums of two positive cubes in two or more ways corresponding to the Pell-type equation X^2 - 3*Y^2 = 56862.
%H A395378 Jamal Agbanwa, <a href="https://doi.org/10.6084/m9.figshare.30390145">Generating Infinitely Many Taxicab Numbers</a>, Figshare, (preprint) 2025.
%F A395378 a(n) = x(n-1)^3 + y(n-1)^3 = u(n-1)^3 + w(n-1)^3 where:
%F A395378   x(n) = (-162 + 27*((15 - 7*sqrt(3))*(7 - 4*sqrt(3))^n + (15 + 7*sqrt(3))*(7 + 4*sqrt(3))^n))/4 + 81,
%F A395378   y(n) = (-486 + 27*((7 - 5*sqrt(3))*(7 - 4*sqrt(3))^n + (7 + 5*sqrt(3))*(7 + 4*sqrt(3))^n))/4,
%F A395378   u(n) = (-162 + 27*((15 - 7*sqrt(3))*(7 - 4*sqrt(3))^n + (15 + 7*sqrt(3))*(7 + 4*sqrt(3))^n))/4, and
%F A395378   w(n) = (-486 + 27*((7 - 5*sqrt(3))*(7 - 4*sqrt(3))^n + (7 + 5*sqrt(3))*(7 + 4*sqrt(3))^n))/4 + 243.
%e A395378 For n = 9, a(9) = x(8)^3 + y(8)^3 = 259312805379^3 + 149714317845^3 = 20792758108425527282387330154581064.
